      <title>Moor To The Story: Quicktake on Cisco&apos;s Acquisition of OpenDNS</title>
      <description>This week, Cisco Systems announced its acquisition of OpenDNS for $635M.&amp;nbsp; OpenDNS is a Software as a Service (SaaS) provider for deploying security solutions that enables companies to quickly deploy applications and end-point security solutions to protect themselves and their devices from malware and viruses.&amp;nbsp; This acquisition will help Cisco Systems significantly grow its security profile, especially around the cloud and Internet of Things (IoT).</description>
